HEADWORD: Foreignism
<hw>For"eign*ism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Anything peculiar
to a foreign language or people; a foreign idiom or custom.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>It is a pity to see the technicalities of the so-called liberal
professions distigured by <qex>foreignisms</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Fitzed.
Hall.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

